   "source": [

   "cell_type": "code",

    "ExecuteTime": {

   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from spopt.region.skater import Skater\n",
    "import geopandas as gpd\n",
    "import libpysal\n",
    "from libpysal.examples import load_example\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import pairwise as skm"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "##### Airbnb Spots Clustering in Chicago\n",
    "\n",
    "Cluster 77 communities into 10 regions such that each region consists of at least 3 communities and homogeneity in the number of Airbnb spots in communities is maximized."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2021-01-13T18:46:05.428037Z",
     "start_time": "2021-01-13T18:46:05.423484Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<libpysal.examples.base.Example at 0x16afa9b20>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 4,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "load_example('AirBnB')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2021-01-13T18:46:05.732983Z",
     "start_time": "2021-01-13T18:46:05.429663Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<AxesSubplot:>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 5,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 864x576 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "image/png": {
       "height": 465,
       "width": 406
      },
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "pth = libpysal.examples.get_path('airbnb_Chicago 2015.shp')\n",
    "chicago = gpd.read_file(pth)\n",
    "chicago.plot(column='community', categorical=True, figsize=(12,8), edgecolor='w')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Initialize the parameters"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2021-01-13T18:46:05.945380Z",
     "start_time": "2021-01-13T18:46:05.734938Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "w = libpysal.weights.Queen.from_dataframe(chicago)\n",
    "attrs_name = ['num_spots']\n",
    "n_clusters = 10\n",
    "floor = 3\n",
    "trace = False\n",
    "islands = \"increase\"\n",
    "spanning_forest_kwds = dict(\n",
    "    dissimilarity=skm.manhattan_distances, affinity=None, reduction=np.sum, center=np.mean\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2021-01-13T18:46:06.320869Z",
     "start_time": "2021-01-13T18:46:05.949025Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "model = Skater(chicago, w, attrs_name, n_clusters, floor, trace, islands, spanning_forest_kwds)\n",
    "model.solve()\n",
    "chicago['skater_new'] = model.labels_"
   ]
  },
  {

   "execution_count": 8,
